  "elapsed_s": 8.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Because when the Bulgarians in the 19th century rebelled against the Turks and they were about to be wiped out when the Turks brought their elite army, which was called the [TURKISH], She the Russian Tsar Nikolai, they call him the Liberator, and the have a-- anyway, he came and he helped them defeat the-- the-- the Turks.",
      "word_count": 58
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So Bulgaria would always owe a debt of gratitude to Russian.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was when we get all that information, not after that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'm listening to that as a child and they're telling us that the king was dead.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was-- at that time, the Jews absolutely took it real hard.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they felt very strongly that they was a big part.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I thought it was solely, but I'm not going to get into that controversy.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But they was a big part.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Bottom line is that he did not sign the edict and he paid with his life for it, whatever controversy may be involved after that, and I really don't care.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I do know that the king, the clergy and the Bulgarian people-- a combination of all-- spared the Jews.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Third.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Subsequently, two years ago, his son, who was in exile, King Simeon II, came to Los Angeles and the Jewish National Fund bestowed upon his father the Legion of Honor posthumously for saving the Jews of Bulgaria.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And also a forest on October 21st will be dedicated in honor of the king, the Bulgarian people, and the clergy and the intelligentsia, all these people that were so-- so very much responsible for our-- for our lives.",
      "word_count": 39
    }
  ],
